args:
The prince seeks out the masked woman who
looked like Zethia to get her help in altering
the past. When he finds her, Chronos changes
completely. After learning his true goal all
along was to find and kill the woman, the prince
faces off against his former dragon ally.
I still wasn't able to stop my father.
He changed, just as I knew would happen.\nAnd now Zethia will...
What am I supposed to do? How can\nI actually CHANGE these events?!
Maybe this was a fool's errand all along.
And yet, there is another who does\nthe very thing you seek to do.
Another who has cast off the yoke\nand seeks to disturb causality.
Audric is another, but there is also one\nbesides him—one you have already met.
As you recently experienced, if one goes\nback in time, it is possible for the same\nperson to exist twice in a single timeline.
Now recall, if you will, the moment\nwhen your whole journey started...
The same person existing twice...\nWait, you're right!
There was the masked woman—\nthe one who looked like Zethia!
If you reunite with her, you may well be\nable to introduce a larger change to the\nstream of time.
So if I could convince the other Zethia\nto help me somehow...
All right. Let's do this, Chronos!
I inch ever closer to your\ntrue objective, my liege...
Why have you come here? If you knew\nthe powers you were trifling with...
Stay alert, Brother.\nSomething about her is not right.
Yeah, that much is clear.\n...You there! Identify yourself.
I've no time to bandy about words.\nI will stop you from forging this\ndragonpact, no matter the cost!
There! It's the us from the past.\nAnd there's the masked girl!
At long last, I've made it...
No... No no... He's forged the pact again...\nIs there no changing this?
I can stay here no longer...\nBut I will return!
Wait, what? How? I mean, HUH?!\nThat's Zethia!
But it's also not Zethia, because Zethia\nis standing over there and... WHAAAAT?!
Nnngh...\nYou weren't supposed to find out.
But regardless...our time is up.\nWe will finish this unpleasantness\nanother day.
Now, my liege! Let us follow the Auspex\ninto the space between time and causality!
Yes, but I'm not the brother you just saw.
I'm a time traveler just like you,\nand I also came here to—
To twist time to your own ends!
Now, my liege! Now is the hour where I\nwill finally see your wish realized!
All will be made right now. This is my\ntrue liege's wish—as well as my own.
There is a you who is not you.\nA you who will one day no longer be you.
That man is my true liege, and his will\nis the one I fulfill now.
So the lord you serve is actually...HIM?
Farewell to you, Auspex. You will go to\nyour grave filled with regret for meddling\nin things far beyond your ken.
Chronos! Why are you doing this?!
Ridding the world of the Auspex is the key\nto my true liege's grand ambition.
Wait, WHAT liege?! And what's this\nabout a grand ambition?!
It means you have been manipulated to\nserve his ends, {player_name}.
From the very start, this dragon's goal has\nbeen to find the Auspex—the one who\nloosed herself from the yoke of causality.
As such, he used you to achieve his aim.
Now return to your original time—for you\nare the vessel who will one day become\nmy true liege.
So I'm not your true liege NOW?
Enough. I have no intention of harming\nyou, but you must return to your own time.
And now, Auspex, you will die in order\nto fuel the glory of my liege.
I will not allow this, Chronos!

Will you never learn? The bonds which
remain in that body are but weak dregs.
Soon you will no longer be able to pursue
me as you have been.
Which is why I must use the time\nleft to me to achieve my aims.
A meaningless effort from a fallen king.
You and the Auspex alike will meet your\nend this day. Now accept your fate!
Why do you interfere? Surely you do not\nsee my actions here as betrayal?
It fills me with regret to have\nbeen used by you.
But I tried just as much to use you—and\nyour power—to achieve my own ends.
So I can assign you no blame.
Because I won't hand Zethia over to you!
I came here to protect my sister,\nand that's what I'm going to do!
You are but a vessel for my true liege,\nand for the sake of his glory, I will put\nyou to rest!
